{
  "stem": "13471.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We got hit by a kamikaze off of Okinawa, and I came home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was in-- I was in-- I was in San Diego waiting for the Navy to decide what to do next with this damaged ship when they dropped the A-bomb.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They sent me out to Saipan, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I was to be a control vessel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, when you send-- you see these pictures of all these landing craft full of marines heading towards the beach.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, they have to head toward a specific beach, and they have to be guided in, because those guys are ducking bullets.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they have to be backed up, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so they would take this PC of mine-- I was the closest in of any of the ships-- 1,000 yards off the beach.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had to be-- I was off of Green Beach One and Green Beach Two.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was the commanding-- I was the control vessel for those two beaches.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Saipan, right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the boys would come in with these landing craft, and they would line up on me before D-day, before H-hour.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I would line them up this side, line them up this side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when the thing got out, I'd-- boom-- blow the whistle, and they'd take off, you see.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I was the-- I was the radio link between the guys ashore and all of the supplies that were in these floating freighters astern, four or five miles out at sea where they were safe from artillery fire from the islands, you see.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And first, they come through-- well, we need more barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, I knew that barbed wire is in the second hold in AKA such and such.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
